   <title type="text">Syriac Reference Portal Wiki</title>
   <content type="html"><![CDATA[<span style="font-size: x-small;">[First posted in AWOL 3 October 2011. Updated 3 April 2012] </span><br /><br /><a href="http://www.syriac.ua.edu/wiki/index.php5/Main_Page">Syriac Reference Portal&nbsp;</a><br /><blockquote class="tr_bq"><h1> <span style="font-size: x-small;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Welcome_to_the_Syriac_Reference_Portal_Demo_Page.21">Welcome to the Syriac Reference Portal Demo Page!</span></span></h1><span style="font-size: x-small;">Below are links demonstrating the reference tools we are building. </span><br /><span style="font-size: x-small;">Please note that this site is still under construction. If you  encounter broken links, please contact syriac@ua.edu for assistance. </span><br /><span style="font-size: x-small;">You will find a general discussion of the Portal and its aims here: </span><br /><ul><li> <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a class="external text" href="http://syriac.ua.edu/" rel="nofollow">Syriac Reference Portal General Information Page</a></span></li></ul><span style="font-size: x-small;">You will find a sample article with live text and a prosopography entry here: </span><br /><ul><li> <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a href="http://www.syriac.ua.edu/wiki/index.php5/Philoxenos_of_Mabbug" title="Philoxenos of Mabbug">Philoxenos of Mabbug</a> Sample Article (This article may be locked if we are testing the site.) </span></li></ul><span style="font-size: x-small;">Mock up demos (i.e. not live text) of the same are available here: </span><br /><ul><li> <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a class="external text" href="http://syriac.ua.edu/person.html" rel="nofollow">Prosopography Browser</a></span></li><li> <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a class="external text" href="http://syriac.ua.edu/entry.html" rel="nofollow">Encyclopedia and Bibliography Demo</a></span></li></ul><span style="font-size: x-small;">The bibliography module for the site is in progress here: </span><br /><ul><li> <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a class="external text" href="http://biblio.syriac.ua.edu/" rel="nofollow">Online Bibliography</a></span></li></ul><span style="font-size: x-small;">We are also partnering with Beth Mardutho, the Syriac Institute to create an online publication repository: </span><br /><ul><li> <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a class="external text" href="http://ebetharke.bethmardutho.org/" rel="nofollow">ebeth arke public domain repository (running an DSpace installation)</a></span></li></ul><span style="font-size: x-small;">Sample entries for our manuscript catalogue (using TEI/ENRICH) are here: </span><br /><ul><li> <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a class="external text" href="http://syriac.ua.edu/WrightDCCXLIX.xml" rel="nofollow">Syriac Manuscript Catalogue Sample TEI Entry 1</a></span></li><li> <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a class="external text" href="http://syriac.ua.edu/WrightDCCL.xml" rel="nofollow">Syriac Manuscript Catalogue Sample TEI Entry 2</a></span></li><li> <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a class="external text" href="http://syriac.ua.edu/WrightDCCLI.xml" rel="nofollow">Syriac Manuscript Catalogue Sample TEI Entry 3</a></span></li></ul><span style="font-size: x-small;">Finally, we are partnering with OCLC World Cat to create a Syriac authority file (or list of Syriac authors). </span><br /><ul><li> <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a class="external text" href="http://viaf.org/" rel="nofollow">Virtual International Authority File (Collaborator Website)</a></span></li><li> <span style="font-size: x-small;"><a class="external text" href="http://viaf.org/hosted/syriac/" rel="nofollow">Syriac Extension of Viaf (search for "Philoxenos")</a></span></li></ul><span style="font-size: x-small;">Thank you for your interest! </span><br /><span style="font-size: x-small;">-David Michelson, project director </span><br /><span style="font-size: x-small;">Postscript for the curious: The acronym of the Portal (SRP) when rendered in Syriac as above spells "srophe" or seraphim. </span></blockquote><br />]]></content>
